Events.html: 98 – Trajan succeeded his adoptive father Nerva as Roman emperor; under his rule the Roman Empire would reach its maximum extent.

Events.html: 1142 – Song Dynasty General Yue Fei is executed.

Events.html: 1186 – Henry VI, the son and heir of the Holy Roman Emperor Frederick I, marries Constance of Sicily.

Events.html: 1302 – Dante Alighieri, the poet and politician is exiled from Florence, Italy, where he served as one of six priors governing the city.
Events.text: Dante Alighieri, the poet and politician is exiled from Florence, Italy, where he served as one of six priors governing the city.

Events.html: 1343 – Pope Clement VI issues the papal bull Unigenitus to justify the power of the pope and the use of indulgences. Nearly 200 years later, Martin Luther would protest this.

Events.html: 1593 – The Vatican opens the seven-year trial of scholar Giordano Bruno.

Events.html: 1606 – Gunpowder Plot: The trial of Guy Fawkes and other conspirators begins, ending with their execution on January 31.
Events.text: Gunpowder Plot: The trial of Guy Fawkes and other conspirators begins, ending with their execution on January 31.

Events.html: 1695 – Mustafa II becomes the Ottoman sultan in Istanbul on the death of Ahmed II. Mustafa rules until his abdication in 1703.

Events.html: 1776 – American Revolutionary War: Henry Knox's "noble train of artillery" arrives in Cambridge, Massachusetts.

Events.html: 1785 – The University of Georgia is founded, the first public university in the United States.
Events.text: The University of Georgia is founded, the first public university in the United States.

Events.html: 1825 – The U.S. Congress approves Indian Territory (in what is present-day Oklahoma), clearing the way for forced relocation of the Eastern Indians on the "Trail of Tears".

Events.html: 1868 – Boshin War: The Battle of Toba-Fushimi between forces of the Tokugawa shogunate and pro-Imperial factions begins, which will end in defeat for the shogunate, and is a pivotal point in the Meiji Restoration.
Events.text: Boshin War: The Battle of Toba-Fushimi between forces of the Tokugawa shogunate and pro-Imperial factions begins, which will end in defeat for the shogunate, and is a pivotal point in the Meiji Restoration.

Events.html: 1869 – Boshin War: Tokugawa rebels establish the Ezo Republic in Hokkaidō.

Events.html: 1870 – The Kappa Alpha Theta fraternity is founded at DePauw University.

Events.html: 1927 – Ibn Saud takes the title of King of Nejd.

Events.html: 1939 – First flight of the Lockheed P-38 Lightning.
Events.text: First flight of the Lockheed P-38 Lightning.

Events.html: 1943 – World War II: The VIII Bomber Command dispatched ninety-one B-17s and B-24s to attack the U-Boat construction yards at Wilhelmshaven, Germany. This was the first American bombing attack on Germany of the war.

Events.html: 1944 – World War II: The 900-day Siege of Leningrad is lifted.

Events.html: 1967 – The United States, United Kingdom, and Soviet Union sign the Outer Space Treaty in Washington, D.C., banning deployment of nuclear weapons in space, and limiting use of the Moon and other celestial bodies to peaceful purposes.
